The paper deals with deep metric learning, which is a subfield of machine learning that involves learning a distance metric between data points. This is typically applied to computer vision tasks such as image retrieval and clustering, which suggests that the paper could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also proposes a new approach to solving the distance metric learning problem, which involves projecting onto feasible sets, suggesting that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on several datasets, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.MM, and cs.IR, in that order.
